createExternalProxy

public IExternalProxy createExternalProxy()
Create an external proxy object in memory. This object will be in the working copy state, so it can be modified and saved.

Returns:
a new external proxy object in its default state

createExternalState

public IExternalState createExternalState()
Create an object to attach replicated external state to.

NOTE: this method is only for use by the interop client library, not by clients of the library. The ExternalState type is intended to be hidden, but the client library needs to create such objects to pass to the server.

Returns:
a new ExternalState object in its default state
